tweet: Recently, I met with Florida Agriculture Commissioner Nikki Fried & State Forester & Director of the Florida Forest Service Jim Karels. We discussed how the state & federal governments can work together to help our farmers, foresters, and ranchers recover from Hurricane Michael.

Today, I questioned @USDA @SecretarySonny on the agency's response to Hurricane Michael. Many crops in the Panhandle were devastated by the storm and I am committed to ensuring we take care of our farmers, ranchers, and foresters. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bIoSYuzKOt0&feature=youtu.be …

Last week I also spent time meeting with students at St. John Paul II Catholic School. We discussed our faith and how that drives us in our every day lives. Thank you to Principal Joanna Copenhaver for a great afternoon! pic.twitter.com/NbwAetfz8m
Thank you to Executive Director Emily Ketring for working hard to keep the youth in North Florida supported and engaged. 2/2 pic.twitter.com/m2jlibfyDd

Last week, I had the opportunity to spend time with the Boys andGirls Club of North Central Florida in Perry. I had a great time meeting all of the young people who are thriving because of this organization. 1/2 pic.twitter.com/DBOfQVxtDp
As Chairwoman of the @AppropsDems Subcommittee on Military Construction @RepDWStweets is committed to helping us rebuild and I thank her for the continued support. pic.twitter.com/2FMhgXqxTX

On Tuesday, @RepDWStweets joined me for a tour & briefing at @NSAPC12 & @USCG Station PC. We surveyed damage from Hurricane Michael & discussed the needs of our military in the Panhandle. pic.twitter.com/LuZSaMnXQA

Last week, I visited w/ students from Holy Comforter Episcopal School. These students traveled to DC from Tallahassee to learn about our 3 branches of government. These students had great questions on my work in Congress & told me their thoughts on the recent govt shutdown. pic.twitter.com/ZdrD2UDKdj

This bill falls short of providing necessary funding to secure our borders and is forcing @POTUS to declare a national emergency to get the job done. I believe we can and must do better. 6/6
Furthermore, Democrats promised they would work with @realDonaldTrump to address border security - a promise they did not keep. 5/6

Florida’s Panhandle needs help now, not six months down the road. It’s been 4 months since Hurricane Michael hit & much of the Panhandle is still in ruins, with people living in tents & surviving on the bare essentials. We need to pass disaster funding & we need to do it now. 4/6
I cannot in good conscience support a bill that completely ignores all those who were devastated by disasters in 2018. We cannot continue to kick the can down the road on disaster funding. 3/6

It includes no money for Hurricane Michael disaster relief, does not seriously address the humanitarian crisis at our border, & was finalized at the last minute with little time for members to review the details. 2/6
The spending deal worked out by House and Senate leadership fails to address the needs of those in North Florida. 1/6
Today we remember the lives that were tragically cut short in Parkland one year ago today. Our hearts go out to Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School community.

We discussed a new workforce development program in the city and the different steps he is taking to improve Tallahassee. .@MayorOfTLH has been actively working to instill real change in Tallahassee and I believe he is moving in the right direction. pic.twitter.com/u3kmMPC9kF
